    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="2"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d2">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.34553B/72</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The American Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Portuguese Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Salazar</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="5" xml:id="d2fn1">Copy transmitted to the Department in
                        despatch 154, January 26, from Lisbon; received February 3.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-07">January 7,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have today received a telegram<note
                        n="6" xml:id="d2fn2">Telegram 43, January 6, 1944, not printed.</note> from
                    the Secretary of State indicating that he, the Secretary of War,<note n="7"
                        xml:id="d2fn3">Henry L. Stimson.</note> and the Secretary of the Navy<note
                        n="8" xml:id="d2fn4">Frank Knox.</note> concur in the suggestion that an
                    American commercial company should conduct the survey of the Azores, which we
                    discussed on the last day of December. They are also in agreement that Pan
                    American Airways, Inc. is the best equipped commercial organization to undertake
                    this task. That Company has been informally and confidentially consulted and its
                    acceptance obtained in advance should it be selected to do this work.</p>
                <p>I thought that it might prove a convenience to you if I sent you this information
                    in writing. At the same time, I wish to ask for an appointment to see you at
                    your earliest convenience.</p>
                <p>Please accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>R. <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Norweb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
